def plot_graph(G):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
    pos=nx.spring_layout(G)
    nx.draw(G, with_labels = True, pos = pos)
    plt.show(True)

def read_graph(filepath):
    G= nx.read_edgelist(filepath, nodetype=int, comments='%') # Read the network
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

def read_gml_graph(filepath):
    M= nx.read_gml(filepath) # Read the network
    G = nx.Graph()
    for u,v,data in M.edges(data=True):
        w = data['weight'] if 'weight' in data else 1.0
        if G.has_edge(u,v):
            G[u][v]['weight'] += w
        else:
            G.add_edge(u, v, weight=w)
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

def read_digraph(filepath):
    G= nx.read_edgelist(filepath, create_using=nx.DiGraph, nodetype=int, comments='%') # Read the network
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

def read_graph_weighted(filepath):
    G= nx.read_edgelist(filepath, nodetype=int, data=(('weight',float),), comments='%') # Read the network
    Gcc=sorted(nx.connected_component_subgraphs(G), key = len, reverse=True)
    G=Gcc[0]
    G = nx.convert_node_labels_to_integers(G, first_label=0)
    N = len(G)
    M = G.number_of_edges()
    print('Number of nodes:', N)
    print('Number of edges:', M)
    return G

Functions for the centrality measures¶

In [42]:
def degree_centrality(G):
    vk = dict(G.degree())
    vk = list(vk.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(vk, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Degree Centrality", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(k)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Degree Centrality (k)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)
    return vk

def closeness_centrality(G):
    CLC = dict(nx.closeness_centrality(G))
    CLC = list(CLC.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(CLC, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Closeness Centrality", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(CLC)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Closeness Centrality (CLC)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)
    return CLC

def betweenness_centrality(G):
    B = dict(nx.betweenness_centrality(G))
    B = list(B.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(B, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the betweenness centrality", fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(B)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Betweenness centrality (B)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)
    return B

def page_rank(G):
    PR = dict(nx.pagerank(G, alpha=0.85))
    PR = list(PR.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(PR, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the PageRank", fontsize = 20)
    plt.ylabel("P(PR)", fontsize = 20)
    plt.xlabel("PageRank (PR)",fontsize = 20)
    plt.show(True)
    return PR

def k_core(G):
    KC= dict(nx.core_number(G))
    KC = list(KC.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(KC, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Core Number", fontsize = 20)
    plt.ylabel("P(KC)", fontsize = 20)
    plt.xlabel("Core Number (KC)", fontsize = 20)
    plt.savefig('kcore.eps')
    plt.show(True)
    return KC

def eigenvector_centrality(G):
    EC = dict(nx.eigenvector_centrality(G, max_iter = 1000))
    EC = list(EC.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(EC, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Eigenvector Centrality",fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(EC)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Eigenvector Centrality (EC)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)
    return EC

def random_walk_accessibility(G):
    RW = dict(nx.current_flow_betweenness_centrality(G, dtype=np.float32))
    RW = list(RW.values())
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(RW, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Random Walk Accessibility",fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(RW)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Random Walk Accessibility (RW)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)
    return RW

def communicability_centrality(G):
    COM = dict(nx.communicability_exp(G))
    COM = list(COM.values())
    returnCOM = []
    for i in range(len(COM[0])):
        returnCOM.append(COM[i][i])
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    plt.hist(returnCOM, density=True)
    plt.title("Distribution of the Communicability Centrality",fontsize=20)
    plt.ylabel("P(COM)", fontsize=20)
    plt.xlabel("Communicability Centrality (COM)", fontsize=20)
    plt.show(True)
    return returnCOM

Function for the correlation matrix¶

In [44]:
def correlation_matrix(vk, CLC, B, EC, PR, KC, RW, COM):
    df = pd.DataFrame({'K':vk,'CLC':CLC,'B':B,'EC':EC,'PR':PR,'KC':KC, 'RW': RW, 'COM': COM})
    corr = df.corr()
    plt.figure(figsize=(8,8))
    plt.imshow(corr, cmap='Blues', interpolation='none', aspect='auto')
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.xticks(range(len(corr)), corr.columns, rotation='vertical', fontsize=20)
    plt.yticks(range(len(corr)), corr.columns, fontsize=20)
    plt.suptitle('Correlation between centrality measures', fontsize=20)
    plt.grid(False)
    plt.show()
